In relational database we store the data across multiple tables by representing relationship between the tables using pk and fk. So in-order to access the data from these tables along their relationship data of the other tables we need to use join queries.
  
How to write a join query?
  The records of 2 tables has to be combined with each other by matching primary key of one table with each of the record foreign key of the other table.
  
There are 3 types of join queries are there
1. inner join = The intersection 2 table records will be returned as an outcome
2. left outer join 
3. right outer join


  